Nightmares of Meloen currently supports two modes for inclusion:
================================================================

   - include Nightmares of Meloen in your own era
     (or an UMC era you have downloaded)

   - include Nightmares of Meloen(dev) in World Conquest MP scenario



Include Nightmares of Meloen in your own era:
-----------------------------------------------
If you want to include Nightmares of Meloen faction in your era, follow the instructions in the file eras/my_era+nightmares.cfg.

The races and traits defined in this add-on are protected (and define) with the following macros:
    RACE_ABERRATION, RACE_ELEMENTAL, RACE_INSECT, RACE_NIGHTMARE
    TRAIT_RUBY, TRAIT_DIAMOND, TRAIT_SAPPHIRE, TRAIT_EMERALD
    TRAIT_INSECT, TRAIT_NIGHTMARE
    UNHATCHED_TRAITS, UNHATCHED_TO_STANDARD_TRAITS

It your own era is using the same traits or races, to avoid conflicts you should protect the definitions in you own era with the same macro.
For a trait, change the lines:

    #define TRAIT_RUBY
        [trait]
            id=ruby
            [...]
        [/trait]
    #enddef

into:

    #ifndef TRAIT_RUBY
    #define TRAIT_RUBY
        [trait]
            id=ruby
            [...]
        [/trait]
    #enddef
    #endif

For a race, change the lines:

    [race]
        id=elemental
        [...]
    [/race]

into:

    #ifndef RACE_ELEMENTAL
    #define RACE_ELEMENTAL
    #enddef
    [race]
        id=elemental
        [...]
    [/race]
    #endif



Include Nightmares of Meloen(dev) in World Conquest:
----------------------------------------------------
NB: The era Default+(dev)Nightmares must be selected for playing World Conquest.

For World Conquest on version 1.10/1.11: in the file ~add-ons/World_Conquest/utils/variables.cfg, 


1- at the end of macro WORLD_CONQUEST_GROUP_DEFINITIONS, add the two lines:
...........................................................................

{~add-ons/Nightmares_of_Meloen/devel/utils/world_conquest.cfg}
{WORLD_CONQUEST_ERA_SPECIFIC_GROUP_DEFINITIONS}


So the code:

    #define WORLD_CONQUEST_GROUP_DEFINITIONS
    [group]
        id=dummy
        leader=none
    [/group]
    [group]
        [...]
    [/group]
    #enddef

should become:

    #define WORLD_CONQUEST_GROUP_DEFINITIONS
    [group]
        id=dummy
        leader=none
    [/group]
    [group]
        [...]
    [/group]
    {~add-ons/Nightmares_of_Meloen/devel/utils/world_conquest.cfg}
    {WORLD_CONQUEST_ERA_SPECIFIC_GROUP_DEFINITIONS}
    #enddef


2- at the end of macro WORLD_CONQUEST_ARTIFACT_DEFINITIONS, add the two lines:
..............................................................................

{~add-ons/Nightmares_of_Meloen/devel/utils/world_conquest.cfg}
{WORLD_CONQUEST_ERA_SPECIFIC_ARTIFACT_DEFINITIONS}


So the code:

    #define WORLD_CONQUEST_ARTIFACT_DEFINITIONS
    [group]
        id=dummy
        leader=none
    [/group]
    [group]
        [...]
    [/group]
    #enddef

should become:

    #define WORLD_CONQUEST_ARTIFACT_DEFINITIONS
    [artifact]
        [...]
    [/artifact]
    {~add-ons/Nightmares_of_Meloen/devel/utils/world_conquest.cfg}
    {WORLD_CONQUEST_ERA_SPECIFIC_ARTIFACT_DEFINITIONS}
    #enddef

